 role, and Columbus's views on the Indians. In doing so she opens up the vast cultural context of the Discovery. Exploring the ways in which the first images of America as seen through European eyes both represented and helped shape the Discovery, she maps the inception and growth of a discourse that was to dominate the colonizing of the New World.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Letters.2bisacsh  a1492.  aappropriation.  aauthenticity.  aauthority.  acartography.  achristopher columbus.  acolonialism.  acolumbus.  adestination.  adiscovery of the americas.  adiscovery.  aexpeditions.  aexploration.  aferdinand.  agender.  aideology.  aindigenous peoples.  aisabela.  ajourney.  alas casas.  alatin america.  alatin american history.  alatin american literature and culture series.  alibro copiador.  aliterary letters.  anative americans.  anative peoples.  apilgrimage.  atestimony.  athe crown.  athe new world.  atravel narratives.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008297740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520913943?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913943423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913943/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY